<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="common-adj">common <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kɒmən/    美 /'kɑːmən/  </p>
<p>[常与more或most连用]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>普遍的；常见的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 uncommon / rare </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>common sense</strong>
常识</p><footer>2010 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It’s common for</strong> people <strong>to</strong> wear masks in foggy days. 
在雾天人们戴口罩很常见。</p></div>

<p>注: common的比较级和最高级有两种形式： commoner / commonest和more common / most common，后者更常用。  </p>
<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>共同的；共有的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the common goal 
共同目标</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Choosing friends with common interests is important in building friendship. 
选择志趣相投的朋友对建立友谊很重要。</p><footer>2012 辽宁改</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>普通的；寻常的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the common people 
平民百姓</p></div>

<h3 id="common-normal-ordinary-usual">辨析 common, normal, ordinary, usual</h3>
<p><strong>common</strong> 侧重表示普遍、常见。
<strong>normal</strong> 侧重指“正常的”、“平常的”。
<strong>ordinary</strong> 侧重表示平常、平凡、无奇特之处。形容人时可与common通用。
<strong>usual</strong> 表示由于长时间没有变化而形成了一种习惯或制度，强调习惯性。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He arrived later than usual. 
他到得比平时晚。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is usual for him to sit up late at night. 
他熬夜已成习惯。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>commonly /'kɑːmənli/ adv   </p></div>